TITLE: Filtering High-Value USDT Transfers using Moralis Streams - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to set up a Moralis Stream with advanced filtering to monitor USDT transactions over $1M from a specific address on Ethereum. Dependencies include the Moralis JavaScript SDK, initialized prior to usage. The filter_ERC20 object specifies the sender and minimum transfer value; parameters are used in stream creation followed by attaching the USDT contract address. Expects a valid Moralis API key and prior SDK initialization; outputs new stream id and attaches the monitored address. Only transfers matching the filter trigger webhooks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/docs/04-guides/streams-api-full-guide-walkthrough.md#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
