TITLE: Configuring Moralis Stream for ERC20 Token Transfer Tracking
DESCRIPTION: Sets up a Moralis stream to monitor BUSD token transfers on BSC network. Defines the ERC20 Transfer event ABI, configures stream options with filters for specific token address, and adds wallet addresses to track. Uses webhook for notifications and includes contract logs with specific topic filtering.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/docs/02-streams-api/evm/tutorials/how-to-track-specific-erc20-token-transfers-from-a-list-of-wallets.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const ERC20TransferABI = [
    {
        anonymous: false,
        inputs: [
            {
                indexed: true,
                name: "from",
                type: "address",
            },
            {
                indexed: true,
                name: "to",
                type: "address",
            },
            {
                indexed: false,
                name: "value",
                type: "uint256",
            },
        ],
        name: "Transfer",
        type: "event",
    },
];

// This filter will only listen to BUST token transfers
const filter = {
    eq: [
        "moralis_streams_contract_address",
        "0x55d398326f99059ff775485246999027b3197955",
    ], // BUST contract https://bscscan.com/token/0x55d398326f99059ff775485246999027b3197955
};

const options = {
    chains: ["0x38"],
    description: "Listen to a list of wallets for BUSD transfers",
    tag: "busd-transfers",
