TITLE: Verifying Webhook Signatures in Python
DESCRIPTION: Python implementation for verifying webhook request signatures using Web3 keccak hashing to validate the authenticity of incoming webhook requests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/docs/02-streams-api/evm/webhooks/response-body.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def verify_Signature(req, secret):
    provided_signature = req.headers.get("x-signature")
    if not provided_signature:
        raise TypeError("Signature not provided")

    data = req.data+secret.encode()
    signature = Web3.keccak(text=data.decode()).hex()

    if provided_signature != signature:
        raise ValueError("Invalid Signature")
```

