DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet mirrors the JavaScript example, showing how to use the Moralis SDK to create a filtered stream for USDT transfers above $1M from a specific sender. It defines a filter_ERC20 object and includes advanced options in the created stream. Moralis.Streams.add and Moralis.Streams.addAddress APIs are called for creation and address attachment, respectively. Prerequisites are the Moralis SDK configured for TypeScript and a valid API key. Takes filter conditions as input; the output is the stream id and address association.
