TITLE: Defining Stream Filters with Logical Operators - Moralis Streams API - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to construct a nested filter object in JavaScript for use with Moralis Streams API. This filter selects data based on contract address and value, using combinations of 'or', 'and', 'eq', and 'gte' operators. The filter is intended for stream subscription setup and requires contract addresses and numerical value thresholds as parameters. Returns filtered events matching any of the logical groupings; relies on Moralis Streams supporting these filter objects.
