TITLE: Handling Firestore Blockchain Event Streams using Cloud Functions - Firebase (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code defines a Firebase Cloud Function triggered by writes to a specific Firestore collection ('moralis/txs/LoremIpsum'). The onWrite function reacts to all document changes, checks if the transaction is confirmed, and then performs a custom operation. Dependencies: 'firebase-functions' package and correct initialization in the Firebase backend. Inputs: Change events from the collection. Output: Execution of 'doSomeOperation' when a confirmed transaction is detected. Modify 'collectionName' as needed to target your stream's collection.
