TITLE: Monitoring Wallet Transactions with Moralis Streams (Python)
DESCRIPTION: This Python snippet uses the Moralis SDK to create a stream for monitoring native transactions of a specific wallet address (`0x68b...`) on Ethereum (chain ID `0x1`) and Polygon (chain ID `0x89`). It defines the stream configuration in `create_stream_body`, creates the stream using `streams.evm_streams.create_stream`, and then adds the target address to the newly created stream using `streams.evm_streams.add_address_to_stream`.
