TITLE: Authenticating and Displaying User Session on Component Init - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This async ngOnInit implementation fetches session authentication data from the backend upon component initialization. If the authenticated session exists, it formats the relevant user data for display (excluding the 'iat' field). If not, it redirects to the '/signin' route. It expects axios and Router dependencies, and uses environment configuration. Input is implicit (current user session cookie); output is either session display or navigation redirect.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.0/03-authentication-api/evm/tutorials/how-to-sign-in-with-metamask-angular.md#2025-04-23_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
async ngOnInit() {\n  try {\n    const { data } = await axios.get(\n      `${environment.SERVER_URL}/authenticate`,\n      {\n        withCredentials: true,\n      }\n    );\n\n    const { iat, ...authData } = data; // remove unimportant iat value\n\n    this.session = JSON.stringify(authData, null, 2); // format to be displayed nicely\n  } catch (err) {\n    // if user does not have a \"session\" token, redirect to /signin\n    this.router.navigateByUrl('/signin');\n  }\n}
```

