TITLE: Connecting to MetaMask and Getting Wallet Info (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Defines an asynchronous JavaScript function `connectToMetamask` for the client-side. This function uses Ethers.js to interact with the browser's Ethereum provider (typically MetaMask injected into `window.ethereum`). It requests the user's accounts (`eth_requestAccounts`) and the current chain ID (`eth_chainId`). It then returns an object containing the Ethers `signer` (for signing transactions/messages), the `chain` ID, and the user's primary `account` address.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.0/03-authentication-api/evm/integrations/supabase.md#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const connectToMetamask = async () => {
  const provider = new ethers.providers.Web3Provider(window.ethereum, 'any');

  const [accounts, chainId] = await Promise.all([
    provider.send('eth_requestAccounts', []),
    provider.send('eth_chainId', []),
  ]);

  const signer = provider.getSigner();
  return { signer, chain: chainId, account: accounts[0] };
};
```

