TITLE: Handling Complex Struct Inputs in Solidity for Triggers
DESCRIPTION: Shows a Solidity contract `ComplexContract` with a `Human` struct and a `getFriends` function that takes a `Human` struct as input. This example illustrates how to format trigger `inputs` when dealing with complex data types like structs in Solidity, requiring an array of strings for the struct's fields. Example input format: `inputs: [["Joe", "25", "$from"]]`.
