TITLE: Configuring Firestore Security Rules for Moralis Streams
DESCRIPTION: These Firestore security rules are essential for safeguarding data written by the Moralis Streams extension. They permit read access to documents under the `moralis` path structure (`moralis/{collectionType}/{collectionName}/{id}`) but strictly forbid write access from external users, thereby maintaining data integrity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.0/02-streams-api/evm/integrations/firebase.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: firestore
CODE:
```
rules_version = '2';

service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    match /moralis/{collectionType}/{collectionName}/{id} {
      allow read;
      allow write: if false;
    }
  }
}
```

