TITLE: Normalizing Client IPs for Rate Limiting Middleware in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This function processes the incoming request's IP address by replacing '.' and ':' with '-', ensuring compliance with firebase-functions-rate-limiter's requirement that qualifiers must not contain dots or colons. The output is a normalized string suitable for use as a rate limiter key. Requires firebase-functions for the https.Request type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.0/01-web3-data-api/evm/integrations/firebase-api-calls-from-the-frontend.md#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
// 1.2.3.4 -> 1-2-3-4
function readNormalizedIp(request: functions.https.Request): string {
  return request.ip ? request.ip.replace(/\.|:/g, \"-\") : \"unknown\";
}
```

