TITLE: Fetching NFT Owners with JavaScript/TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use the Moralis SDK in JavaScript or TypeScript to retrieve the owners of an NFT collection. It initializes Moralis, sets up the required parameters, and makes an API call to get the NFT owners.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.0/01-web3-data-api/evm/nft-api/05-NFT Owners/how-to-get-the-owners-of-an-nft-collection.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const Moralis = require("moralis").default;
const { EvmChain } = require("@moralisweb3/common-evm-utils");

const runApp = async () => {
  await Moralis.start({
    apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
    // ...and any other configuration
  });

  const address = "0xa186d739ca2b3022b966194004c6b01855d59571";

	const chain = EvmChain.ETHEREUM;

  const response = await Moralis.EvmApi.nft.getNFTOwners({
      address,
      chain,
  });

  console.log(response.toJSON());
}

runApp();
```

