TITLE: Creating POST Route for Signature Verification in Express.js
DESCRIPTION: Implements a POST endpoint that calls the verify function to validate a signed message. The endpoint expects message and signature parameters in the request body to authenticate the user.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/docs/03-authentication-api/evm/integrations/google-cloud-nodejs-unity.md#2025-04-23_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
app.post("/verify", async (req, res) => {
    try {
      const data = await verify(req.body.message, req.body.signature)
      res.status(200)
      res.json(data)

    } catch (error) {
      // Handle errors
      console.error(error)
      res.status(500)
      res.json({ error: error.message })
    }
})
```

