TITLE: Creating Server Endpoint for Authenticating Session (Node.js)
DESCRIPTION: Defines a GET endpoint `/authenticate` in the Node.js/Express server. This endpoint checks for the presence of the `jwt` cookie in the incoming request. If the cookie exists, it attempts to verify the JWT using `jwt.verify` and the `AUTH_SECRET`. If verification is successful, it sends the decoded user data back to the client. If the cookie is missing or verification fails, it returns a 403 Forbidden status.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.0/03-authentication-api/evm/tutorials/how-to-sign-in-with-metamask-angular.md#2025-04-23_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
app.get("/authenticate", async (req, res) => {
  const token = req.cookies.jwt;
  if (!token) return res.sendStatus(403); // if the user did not send a jwt token, they are unauthorized

  try {
    const data = jwt.verify(token, process.env.AUTH_SECRET);
    res.json(data);
  } catch {
    return res.sendStatus(403);
  }
});
```

