TITLE: Verifying Authentication Signature via Moralis Auth - NodeJS
DESCRIPTION: Provides an asynchronous function verify that validates a user's message and signature using Moralis.Auth.verify. It takes message and signature arguments from the client (after signing), and uses the NETWORK constant as context. Returns verification data confirming user identity. Assumes Moralis SDK is set up and ready for use; required for completing the authentication process from the Unity or other clients.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.0/03-authentication-api/evm/integrations/google-cloud-nodejs-unity.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
async function verify(message, signature) {

    const verifiedData = Moralis.Auth.verify({
        message: message,
        signature: signature,
        network: NETWORK,
    })

    return verifiedData
}
```

