TITLE: Fetching Cross-Chain NFTs with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: TypeScript implementation to retrieve NFTs owned by an address across multiple chains using Moralis SDK. Requires Moralis and @moralisweb3/common-evm-utils packages. Returns NFT data from Ethereum, BSC, and Polygon chains.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.0/01-web3-data-api/evm/wallet-api/03-NFT balance/how-to-get-all-nfts-own-by-an-address-cross-chain.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import Moralis from "moralis";
import { EvmChain } from "@moralisweb3/common-evm-utils";

const runApp = async () => {
  await Moralis.start({
    apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
    // ...and any other configuration
  });

  const allNFTs = [];

  const address = "0x26fcbd3afebbe28d0a8684f790c48368d21665b5";

  const chains = [EvmChain.ETHEREUM, EvmChain.BSC, EvmChain.POLYGON];

  for (const chain of chains) {
    const response = await Moralis.EvmApi.nft.getWalletNFTs({
      address,
      chain,
    });

    allNFTs.push(response);
  }

  console.log(allNFTs);
};

runApp();
```

