TITLE: Retrieving ERC20 Transfers in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: JavaScript implementation to fetch ERC20 token transfers for a specific wallet address using Moralis SDK. Requires Moralis API key and uses the EvmChain.ETHEREUM chain.
SOURCE: https://github.com/moralisweb3/docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.0/01-web3-data-api/evm/wallet-api/06-Transfers/how-to-get-all-erc20-transfers-by-wallet.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const Moralis = require("moralis").default;
const { EvmChain } = require("@moralisweb3/common-evm-utils");

const runApp = async () => {
  await Moralis.start({
    apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
    // ...and any other configuration
  });

  const address = "0x2260fac5e5542a773aa44fbcfedf7c193bc2c599";

  const chain = EvmChain.ETHEREUM;

  const response = await Moralis.EvmApi.token.getWalletTokenTransfers({
    address,
    chain,
  });

  console.log(response.toJSON());
};

runApp();
```

